/V (This Suspicious Activity Report \050SAR\051 is filed to document unusual cash activity and potential structuring involving Global Trade Corp\054 an individual with a Low risk rating\056 The activity was flagged under Alert ALRT\05574599 generated by the ML Risk Model v2 due to unusual cash patterns and multiple day deposits\056 Between March 15\054 2024\054 and April 15\054 2024\054 the subject engaged in a series of cash deposits followed by immediate wire transfers\054 totaling approximately \04445\054000\056 On March 18\054 2024\054 a cash deposit of \0449\054500 was made\054 followed by a wire transfer to a destination account in Miami\054 FL\056 This was succeeded by another cash deposit of \0449\054800 on March 25\054 2024\054 with a subsequent wire transfer to a different beneficiary\056 Additional transactions included a cash deposit of \0449\054700 on April 2\054 2024\054 and a wire transfer\054 followed by a \0449\054900 cash deposit on April 10\054 2024\054 again resulting in a wire transfer to another beneficiary\056 The final transaction occurred on April 15\054 2024\054 with a cash deposit of \0446\054200 and an immediate wire transfer\054 completing a pattern of structured transactions designed to avoid Currency Transaction Report \050CTR\051 thresholds\056 The rapid movement of funds\054 lack of apparent business purpose\054 and the subject\047s refusal to explain the large cash deposits raise concerns regarding potential money laundering activities\056 This report is submitted for further regulatory review\056)
/DA (\057HeBo 9 Tf 0 g)
/FT /Tx
/Type /Annot
/Ff 4096
